The paper discusses a numerical polynomial solver in Julia, which falls under the category of numerical analysis (cs.NA). It also mentions providing an algorithmic environment for researchers to design and perform experiments, which could fall under scientific computing (cs.SC) or systems and control (cs.SY). The use of polynomial equations could also relate to dynamical systems (cs.DS). Finally, the use of Julia as the programming language could relate to machine learning (cs.LG), as Julia is becoming increasingly popular in that field.
